1. e4 e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bc4 Bc5 4. b4 Bxb4 5. c3 Ba5 6. d4 exd4 7. O-O d3?! (7... Nge7 $15 { Modern master approved move }) 8. Qb3 { [%cal Gb3f7] } 8... Qf6 9. e5 Qg6 (9... Nxe5?? 10. Re1 { [%cal Ge1e8] } 10... d6 11. Nxe5 dxe5 12. Qa4+ { [%cal Ga4a5] }) 10. Re1 Nge7 11. Ba3 b5?! { Giving back a pawn to gain a tempo, but black soon loses the tempo anyway } (11... d5 12. exd6 cxd6 $15 { [%cal Ge8g8] }) 12. Qxb5 Rb8 13. Qa4 Bb6 14. Nbd2 Bb7? (14... O-O! $10 15. Ne4!? d5! 16. exd6 cxd6 17. Bxd3 Bh3 $10) 15. Ne4 Qf5?? (15... O-O? 16. Bxd3 { [%cal Ge4f6] }) (15... d2!? 16. Re2 O-O $14) 16. Bxd3 { [%cal Gd3f5] } 16... Qh5 17. Nf6+! (17. Ng3 Qh6 18. Rad1 $18 { Simple chess leads to a winning position. Bc1 is the threat, trapping the queen. }) 17... gxf6 18. exf6 Rg8 19. Rad1!! Qxf3?? { The most natural move in the position, but a complete blunder - Black threatens mate but misses white's incredible mating idea. } { [%cal Ge1e7,Gc6e7] } (19... Qh3! 20. Bf1 Qf5 $10) 20. Rxe7+! Nxe7 21. Qxd7+!! Kxd7 22. Bf5+ { [%csl Gc8,Gd8] } 22... Ke8 (22... Kc6 23. Bd7#) 23. Bd7+ Kf8 (23... Kd8 24. fxe7#) 24. Bxe7# *


