1. g3 e5 2. Nf3?! e4 3. Nd4 d5 4. d3 exd3 5. Qxd3 (5. cxd3!? $10 { Leading to a reverse Alekhine defense is probably best. }) 5... Nf6 6. Bg2 Bb4+?! { This move instead helps white develop more pieces } (6... c5!? 7. Nb5 a6 8. N5c3 d4 9. Ne4 Nc6 $15 { Probably objectively best to build a strong center. }) 7. Bd2 Bxd2+ 8. Nxd2 O-O 9. c4 Na6 { [%cal Ga6b4,Gb4d5] } 10. cxd5 Nb4 11. Qc4 Nbxd5 12. N2b3 c6 13. O-O Re8 14. Rfd1 Bg4 15. Rd2 Qc8 16. Nc5 Bh3! 17. Bf3 (17. Bxh3?! Qxh3 18. Nxb7? Ng4 { [%cal Gh3h2,Gh2f2] } 19. Nf3 Nde3!! { [%cal Ge3c4,Ge3g2] } 20. fxe3 Nxe3 { [%cal Ge3c4,Ge3g2] } 21. Qxf7+! Kh8! (21... Kxf7?? 22. Ng5+ Kg8 23. Nxh3 $18) 22. Nh4 Rf8! $19 { [%cal Gf8f1] }) 17... Bg4 { [%cal Gf3g4] } 18. Bg2 (18. Bxg4?! Qxg4 19. Nxb7 Ne4 20. Rdd1 Rac8 $10 { Some compensation for the lost pawn }) 18... Bh3 19. Bf3 Bg4 20. Bh1 { White avoids the repetition and goes for the win. } 20... h5 { [%csl Gf3][%cal Gf2f3,Ge2e4] } 21. b4 a6 22. Rc1 h4 23. a4?! { As we shall see, white's minority attack here is just a bit slower than the position required. } (23. e4! Nb6 24. Qc3 $14) 23... hxg3 24. hxg3 Qc7 { [%cal Gc7g3] } 25. b5 axb5 26. axb5 Re3!! 27. Nf3? (27. fxe3?? Qxg3+ 28. Bg2 Nxe3 $19) (27. bxc6?? Rxg3+ 28. fxg3 Qxg3+ 29. Bg2 Ne3 $19) (27. f3?? Qxg3+! 28. Bg2 Nf4 $19) (27. Bf3! { The best defense } 27... Bxf3 28. exf3 cxb5 29. Nxb5 Qa5 { [%csl Gd2] } 30. Rdd1 $10) 27... cxb5! 28. Qxb5 Nc3! { [%cal Gc3b5,Gc3e2] } 29. Qxb7 Qxb7 30. Nxb7 Nxe2+ 31. Kh2!? { [%csl Gc1,Gb7] } (31. Kf1!? Nxg3+ 32. fxg3 Bxf3 33. Bxf3 Rxf3+ $17) 31... Ne4! (31... Rxf3? 32. Bxf3? (32. Rxe2! $10) 32... Bxf3 33. Re1 Ng4+ 34. Kh3 Nxf2+ $19) 32. Rc4 (32. fxe3 Nxd2 33. Nxd2 Nxc1 $17) 32... Nxf2 (32... Nxd2 33. Nxd2 $10) 33. Bg2 Be6 34. Rcc2 Ng4+ 35. Kh3 (35. Kh1? Ra1+ $19) 35... Ne5+! 36. Kh4?? (36. Kh2 Rxf3! { [%cal Gg2f3,Ge5f3,Gf3d2] } 37. Rxe2 Ng4+ 38. Kh3 Ne3+ 39. Kh2 Nxc2 40. Bxf3 Nd4 { White resigned rather than face the following win of a piece. } { [%csl Ge2,Gf3] } 41. Rf2 Nxf3+ 42. Rxf3 Bd5 { [%cal Gd5b3,Gd5f3,Gd5b7] }) 36... Re4+ 37. g4 Rxg4+ 38. Kh5 (38. Kh3 Rh4+ 39. Kxh4 Ng6+ 40. Kg5 f6+ 41. Kxg6 Nf4#) 38... Nf4# *


