1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 b6 4. a3 Bb7 5. Nc3 d5 6. cxd5 Nxd5 7. Qc2 c5 8. e4 Nxc3 9. bxc3 Be7?! (9... Nd7!? 10. Bf4 cxd4 11. cxd4 Rc8 $10) 10. Bb5+! Bc6 11. Bd3 Nd7 12. O-O h6?! { too slow } 13. Rd1 Qc7? (13... O-O 14. d5 exd5 15. exd5 Bb7 (15... Bxd5 16. Bh7+ Kh8 17. Rxd5) 16. c4 $16) 14. d5! exd5 15. exd5 Bxd5 16. Bb5 { We sacrifice the d pawn in order to open up the center while the king is still uncastled } 16... a6? (16... Bc6!? 17. Bf4! Qxf4 18. Bxc6 $16 { [%cal Gc6e8,Gc6a8] }) 17. Bf4! Qxf4 18. Bxd7+ Kxd7 19. Rxd5+ Kc7 { If black gets one more move to bring a rook to the center of the board and keep his king safe, then white's attack will fizzle out. } 20. Re1! Bd6!? (20... Rhe8!? 21. Rf5! Qd6 22. Rxf7 $18 { Qe2 is coming and black cannot hold onto the pinned bishop. }) 21. Rf5! { [%cal Gf4d6] } 21... Qc4 22. Re4! Qb5 23. Rxf7+! Kb8 { Now that black's king has disconnected the two rooks, white's attack effectively plays itself. } 24. Re6 Rd8 25. c4 Qc6 26. Ne5 Qc8 27. Qb1! $18 { Black resigned rather than face Qxb6+ or the following crush: } { [%cal Gb1b6] } 27... b5 28. cxb5 Bxe5!? (28... a5!? 29. Nc6+! Qxc6 30. bxc6+ Kc8 31. Qb7#) 29. bxa6+ Bb2 30. Qxb2+ Qb7 31. Qxb7# *


